c affection as Queen Mother for nearly half a century. Even more influentially, it is the name of her daughter  Queen Elizabeth II  (  b. 1926 )."],"variants":[{"name":"Elisabeth","meanings":["The spelling of   Elizabeth   used in the Authorized Version of the New Testament, and in most modern European languages. This was the name of the mother of John the Baptist (Luke 1:60). Etymologically, the name means ‘God is my oath’, and is therefore identical with <i>Elisheba</i>, the name of the wife of Aaron according to the genealogy at Exodus 6:23. The final element seems to have been altered by association with Hebrew <i>shabbāth</i> ‘Sabbath’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Elizabeth Of Charlecote was born about 1264, in Charlecote, Warwickshire, England, United Kingdom. She married William de Lucy about 1289. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"ABT 1264–":"umbes 1264–Surnud","1260–1359":"1260–1359","1290–1348":"1290–1348","1264–Female":"1264–Surnud","1348":"1348","1359":"1359","ABT 1264":"umbes 1264","ABT 1289":"umbes 1289","1264":"1264","1260":"1260","ABT 1290":"umbes 1290","1290":"1290","Of, Charlecote, Warwickshire, England":"Charlecote, Warwickshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","of Charlecote,Warwickshire,England":"Charlecote, Warwickshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"ABT 1264–":"noin 1264–Kuollut","1260–1359":"1260–1359","1290–1348":"1290–1348","1264–Female":"1264–Kuollut","1348":"1348","1359":"1359","ABT 1264":"noin 1264","ABT 1289":"noin 1289","1264":"1264","1260":"1260","ABT 1290":"noin 1290","1290":"1290","Of, Charlecote, Warwickshire, England":"Charlecote, Warwickshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","of Charlecote,Warwickshire,England":"Charlecote, Warwickshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"ABT 1264–":"environ 1264–Décédée","1260–1359":"1260–1359","1290–1348":"1290–1348","1264–Female":"1264–Décédée","1348":"1348","1359":"1359","ABT 1264":"environ 1264","ABT 1289":"environ 1289","1264":"1264","1260":"1260","ABT 1290":"environ 1